The Vice President met with the UN Secretary-General's Special Representative for Iraq, Ad Melkert, to discuss the United Nations' role in Iraq and the importance of fairness and transparency in the electoral process. They called for due process and respect for the votes cast by the Iraqi electorate, and supported Iraq's Independent High Electoral Commission in conducting a recount in Baghdad with speed and transparency. They also emphasized the importance of observers in the process and discussed the certification and acceptance of election results, as well as timely government formation.